---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="What fabricstack is, who runs it, and how to get in touch."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert">
    <h1>About fabricstack.dev</h1>
    <p>
      fabricstack is a curated catalog of tools, libraries, frameworks, and
      resources for <strong>Microsoft Fabric</strong> and Power BI developers.
      It exists so developers can discover the tooling they need: official
      Microsoft offerings, open-source community projects, and commercial
      products, all in one searchable, filterable, neutral place.
    </p>

    <h2>Who runs it</h2>
    <p>
      fabricstack.dev is built and maintained by <strong>Peer Grønnerup</strong>,
      who writes about Microsoft Fabric and Power BI at
      <a href="https://peerinsights.emono.dk">peerinsights.emono.dk</a>. The
      site is open source on
      <a href="https://github.com/gronnerup/fabricstack">GitHub</a>: site
      code is MIT licensed, and the catalog content is licensed CC&nbsp;BY&nbsp;4.0.
    </p>

    <h2>Contribute</h2>
    <p>
      Know a tool that belongs here? <a href="/submit">Submit it</a>. Spotted an
      error? Use the <strong>Suggest edit</strong> link on any tool page.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
